title: Presidential Nominations sent to the Senate, 05-12-2009 | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House




May 12, 2009

 



Presidential Nominations sent to the Senate, 05-12-2009




 THE WHITE HOUSE Office of the Press Secretary  ____________________________________________________  For Immediate Release                             May 12, 2009 NOMINATIONS SENT TO THE SENATE:  William J. Wilkins, of the District of Columbia, to be Chief Counsel for the Internal Revenue Service and an Assistant General Counsel in the Department of the Treasury, vice Donald Korb, resigned. Jeffrey D. Zients, of the District of Columbia, to be Deputy Director for Management, Office of Management and Budget, vice Clay Johnson, III, resigned.
